                    </div>
                    <span>I received my copy of "Patents: Ingenious Inventions" last week and have already flown through it cover to cover. It is just the right mix of intelligent information and humor to keep just about anyone interested. Another great asset is the numerous topics the book covers. My personal favorite was the chapter on genetic engineering, but there are so many I am sure others will have different favorites. I really recommend this book to anyone with an inquisitive mind and a funny bone. Enjoy!</span>
                  
              
